Lille m. Richard Sutkell
In onswer to yd of 10 sch. referre you to mine of yeaserday in the meane whil
I finde my bill actrned for non acceptance by which you de monstrate what
effert yd word should have taken, in case I sad payd for H.C. what you ordred
mee to do are you not a shamed to persuade mee in yd freind, so trest
so deeply as I have been & am still, & to refuse £100- for Him nay had you
no effects of mine in yd dandes, you might have don so for him, butt as last
not in my regarde, perhaps you beleave that itt is a bill preforme,
assure you I have recd the valeu from the van first day, sere S resurne itt
& in case you do not send itt back with acceptace towards minday, you
maij assure yd. self & m. sollies, that £ 200- which de dadee drawne on me

Icq meijnde mondelinghs den ul van 10 deser gisteren te beapwoorden, dogh alsoo
ul iude kercke was, & icq maer een ene tijt en hadde, heb icq ul niet connen spreeken
ul heeft maer ƒ5- afgedongen op de 4st poinet de malines aen mij gesonden, icq
dencke, dat de dagentiens daer ul die van heeft die sullen te vreden sijn niet
tegenstaende wederom te neemen, want nu seg 't een goet bij 't ander ien, soo
bevinde, dat seg gistenen hebbe gecoght tot ƒ 59- een coove, soo goet, sijnde winder
als die van ul tot ƒ74-, oversulckx soude seg versoecken de selve wederom te seijnden
ten minsten eenen van de 2, want daer bij anders geen danck sal haelen. ul gelieft
in dat warck voor mij geen meerder te besorgen, ter wijlen ul antw. verwaghte blijve

naesten ul adviseeren, ter wijlen hier beneffens aen ul remitt £101- bco tee laste da

Lille mr. Henry Collier
mij last to you was on the 9 curtt. sence non from you, yett I hope you are safe arrived
att Lille, though m. southell in dis laeder, of the 24 makes no mediton there of, I have
been att Brussel where I found de bustijnes of vale compoted att 40 , & sin mother in
las sicuritie as by the inclosed coppaye you may see, m Sabbarton intends to be in England
within 3 weekes, & will then tell you more particolars, I have delivered iyd
procuration, m. soushell hach sesurned my bill accopted, so have accepted yd., butt finde
yd. sonnes letter of the 2 cur, advising of an other £100- which m kinghtley hach
drawne, truly m. Collus you do not fariely for yd & my intrest, I do not supose
that now you will blame mee for refusal, for whilst you will not leave of whee
